<edge source="concept.abstinence" target="concept.virtue" id="edge.food_drink.concept.abstinence.species_of.concept.virtue">
  <data key="d6">edge.food_drink.concept.abstinence.species_of.concept.virtue</data>
  <data key="d7">tue nor a virtuous act, but something indifferent. Secondly, it may be taken as regulated by reason, and then it signifies either a virtuous habit or a virtuous act. This is the meaning of Peter's words quoted above, where he says that we ought "to join abstinence with knowledge</data>
  <data key="d8">concept.virtue</data>
  <data key="d9">Virtue</data>
  <data key="d10">virtue</data>
  <data key="d11">species_of</data>
