  <data key="d7">ition of the effects of the vices opposed to the parts of temperance . Thus the effect of anger , which is opposed to meekness, is sometimes that a man goes on to commit murder (and this is forbidden in the Decalogue ), and sometimes that he refuses due honor to his parents,</data>
